tadKVnhzXNafFmuEz8=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering field loading in tests**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to use getDeclaredFields directly in tests for loading, since the public API requires it. I could avoid using fields by creating new Field[0], but this might still call the system if the resource is non-null. A dynamic resource would be better if it actually exists. I know I need to call load with fields from the class, and then utilizing Properties.load and field.set within MessagesProperties gives additional coverage. However, I’m wondering about the implications for Graal native metadata for test class fields and user-code-filtering too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CF2nkgmUZzfPWRzc8ha8SACm|fc_0cfd9fd1f576220a0169f0ea01b58c819c8af097ed9ba35539", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.eclipse.jdt/ecj/3.26.0/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1154, "output": 908, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24590, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777396210003, "responseId": "resp_0cfd9fd1f576220a0169f0e9f2c714819c8a541ec991660add"}}
